# Emissary — admin handoff for `{{MAILBOX}}`

An operator has set up **Emissary**, a governed Microsoft 365 mailbox identity for
an automated agent. They need an Exchange Online + Entra administrator to complete
the steps below. Everything is scoped to a **single shared mailbox** — this app
cannot reach any other mailbox once the RBAC scope is in place.

**This identity's capabilities: {{CAPABILITIES_SUMMARY}}.**

## Values

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Tenant | `{{TENANT_ID}}` |
| App (client) ID | `{{CLIENT_ID}}` |
| Shared mailbox | `{{MAILBOX}}` |
| App display name | `{{APP_DISPLAY_NAME}}` |
{{#SEND}}| Allowlist group | `{{ALLOWLIST_GROUP}}` |
{{/SEND}}| Management scope | `{{SCOPE_NAME}}` |
| Mailbox tag | `{{CUSTOM_ATTR}} = {{CUSTOM_ATTR_VALUE}}` |
{{#SEND}}| Transport rule | `{{TRANSPORT_RULE_NAME}}` |
{{/SEND}}| Cert thumbprint (SHA-256) | `{{THUMBPRINT}}` |

## What the operator has already done

- Created the certificate locally (private key never leaves their machine, `chmod 600`).
- Registered (or will register) the single-tenant Entra app and uploaded the **public**
  certificate to it.

## What you need to do

1. **Confirm the app registration** `{{CLIENT_ID}}` exists (single-tenant) and that the
   operator's public certificate is uploaded under *Certificates & secrets → Certificates*.
   The thumbprint should match `{{THUMBPRINT}}`. **No client secrets** — remove any that exist.

2. **Grant + consent to these Graph *application* permissions** (Entra → the app →
   API permissions → Grant admin consent):
   - `{{MAIL_GRAPH_PERMISSIONS}}` — mailbox access (narrowed to one mailbox by step 4 below).
{{#SEND}}   - `GroupMember.Read.All`, `Group.Read.All` — read the allowlist group's membership.
   - `User.ReadBasic.All` — resolve member users' addresses.
   - `OrgContact.Read.All` — resolve mail-contact members.
{{/SEND}}
3. **Find the Enterprise Application Object ID.** Entra → *Enterprise applications* →
   `{{APP_DISPLAY_NAME}}` → Overview → **Object ID**. This is **not** the app
   registration's Object ID and **not** the Client ID. Paste it into `setup-admin.ps1`
   as `$EnterpriseAppObjectId`. (This is the single most common setup mistake — see
   `references/setup.md`.)

4. **Run `setup-admin.ps1`** (rendered alongside this file). It creates the Exchange
   service principal, tags the mailbox, builds the management scope, and assigns the
   role(s) this identity needs ({{MAIL_GRAPH_PERMISSIONS}}){{#SEND}}. It also ensures the
   allowlist group exists and installs the transport rule{{/SEND}}. It is idempotent —
   safe to re-run.

5. **Tell the operator to run `emissary doctor`.** It verifies token acquisition and
   mailbox read, the negative test (proving the app is *blocked* from other mailboxes,
   if a negative-test mailbox was configured){{#SEND}}, and allowlist resolution{{/SEND}}.
